Man, 25, was born at the Luton and Dunstable Hospital in September 1989 .
He was readmitted three months later, suffering a serious brain haemorrhage .
Doctors failed to administer a vitamin K injection to help blood clot and prevent internal bleeding .
Vitamin is given to newborn babies to reduce their risk of blood clots .
The man now requires 24-hour care and will do for the rest of his life .